										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div class="post-section">
<article class="post-31420 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-latest-jobs ast-article-single" style="height: auto !important;">
<div class="ast-post-format- single-layout-1 ast-no-date-box" style="height: auto !important;">
<header class="entry-header ">
<h1 class="entry-title"><span style="color: #ff00ff;">RRB NTPC Graduate Level CBT-I Exam City Details 2026</span></h1>
<p><strong>Author:</strong> Sarkari Exam Team<br />
<strong>Tag:</strong> Graduate pass Job</p>
</header>
<p><!-- .entry-header --></p>
<div class="entry-content clear" style="height: auto !important;">
<div class="post-desc">
<p><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #ff0000;"><strong>Short Information :</strong> <a style="color: #ff0000;" href="https://sarkariresult.com.cm/rrb-ntpc-graduate-level-2026/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Railway Recruitment Board (RRB)</a></span> has released the Exam City Details for the on Technical Popular Categories NTPC Graduate Level Post on the official website of RRB. This recruitment was released for 5810 posts. Applications for the RRB NTPC Graduate Level Recruitment 2025 were accepted from 21 October 2025, to 27 November 2025. CBT Examination Going to conducted from 16-27 march 2026. Candidates who have applied for this recruitment can check their Railway RRB NTPC  Graduate Level Exam City Details 2026 from the link provided below.</span></p>
</div>
<div class="newtable1">
<table style="font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; width: 100%;" width="100%">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td colspan="4" width="100%">
<h2 style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #ff0000;">Railway Recruitment Board (RRB)</span></h2>
<h2 style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #008000;">RRB NTPC Graduate Level CBT-I Exam Date 2026</span></h2>
<h2 style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #ff0000;">RRB NTPC Graduate Level CEN 06/2025</span></h2>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="pd-0" colspan="4" width="100%">
<h3 align="center"><span style="color: #000000;"><b>Important Dates (Tentative) </b></span></h3>
<ul>
<li><span style="color: #000000; font-size: 12pt;">Application Start Date : <strong>21 October 2025</strong></span></li>
<li><span style="color: #000000; font-size: 12pt;">Last Date : <strong>27 November 2025 (Extended)</strong></span></li>
<li><span style="color: #000000; font-size: 12pt;">Fee Payment Last Date : <strong>27 November 2025</strong></span></li>
<li><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #000000;">Correction / Modified Form : <b>30 November 2025 to 09 December 2025</b></span></li>
<li><span style="color: #000000; font-size: 12pt;">Application Status : <b>20 January 2026</b></span></li>
<li><span style="color: #000000; font-size: 12pt;">Exam Date CBT-I : <b>16-27 March 2026</b></span></li>
<li><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Exam City Details : <strong>10 Days Before Exam</strong></span></li>
<li><span style="color: #000000; font-size: 12pt;">Admit Card : <strong>04 Days Before Exam</strong></span></li>
</ul>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="pd-0" colspan="4" width="100%">
<h3 align="center"><span style="color: #000000;"><b>Application Fee</b></span></h3>
<ul>
<li><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #000000;">General, OBC, EWS : <strong>Rs. 500/-</strong></span></li>
<li><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #000000;">SC, ST, PH : <strong>Rs. 250/-</strong></span></li>
<li><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #000000;">All Category Female :<strong> Rs. 250/-</strong></span></li>
<li><span style="font-size: 12pt; background-color: #ffff00; color: #000000;"><strong>Fee Refund (After Appearing in Stage I Exam)</strong></span></li>
<li><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #000000;">General, OBC, EWS : <strong>Rs. 400/-</strong></span></li>
<li><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #000000;">SC, ST, PH : <strong>Rs. 250/-</strong></span></li>
<li><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #000000;">All Category Female :<strong> Rs. 250/-</strong></span></li>
<li><span style="color: #000000; font-size: 12pt;">Candidates have to pay their Examination Fee Through Debit Card / Credit Card / Net Banking / UPI and Other Fee Payment Mode Only.</span></li>
</ul>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="pd-0" colspan="4" width="100%">
<h3 style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #000000;"><strong>RRB NTPC Graduate Level Notification 2025 : Age Limit</strong></span></h3>
<ul>
<li><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong><span style="color: #000000;">Age Limit As On 01 January 2026</span></strong></span></li>
<li><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Minimum Age : <strong>18 Years</strong></span></li>
